2. Notes from LinkedIn course:- On Whiteboarding
URL: https://www.linkedin.com/learning/the-pre-sales-engineer-s-guide-to-whiteboarding-engaging-executives-to-close-deals 
	 a. Whiteboarding - create impact - visual rep
	 b. Sales/Deal cycle:
	  1) Qualification
	  2) Discovery
	  3) Analyzing
	  4) Designing
	  5) Presentation
	  6) Demonstration
	  7) Proposal
	  8) Negotiation
	 c. Whiteboard approach towards "Business drivers":
		 1) Increase Revenue - how does your prod/svc increase revenue?
		 2) Decrease costs - how does your product/service decrease costs?
		 3) Reducing Risks - what are ways your product/service reduces risk?
		 4) Increase impact (around ESG) - Env, Social & Governance 
	 d. Tailor your Whiteboarding approach to the audience:
		a) Visionary CEO - current state vs future state (growth, strategy, ROI, market share)
		b) Tech Savvy CTO - architecture, security, scalability, performance
		c) Customer centric CMO - enhance customer experience, improve lead generation, conversion rates, CSAT
		d) Always back it with data.
	e. Presentation Queue:
		Tell, Write, Tell
    f. Whiteboard Toolkit - Markers, Clean white board, Sticky notes (diff colors)		
    g. Virtual whiteboard platforms:
		    a) https://miro.com 
		    b) https://www.jeda.ai
		    c) www.canva.com
		    d) MS Visio
	 h. Use ICONS to make it engaging and get your message through. 
